sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2132100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: It contains all the necessary subunits for FeFe hydrogenase from Clostridium. acetobutylicum.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shijie Gu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Clostridium acetobutylicum. However, in our project, it is synthesized.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2132005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: HydA with SpyTag, Histag and TEV site
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a modified protein, we added Histag and TEV site to the N-terminal site of hydA, and SpyTag to the C-terminal site of hydA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: YIFAN CHEN
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence of hydA hydrogenase gene is from the chromosome of Clostridium acetobutylicum ATCC 824.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We used Histag for protein purification and added the TEV site so that it will be easy to cut off the attached Histag.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K416002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The antibody for the c-myc transcription factor. This protein binds to Enhancer Box sequences and recruits histone acetyltransferases, serving as a traditional transcription factor and a regulator of global chromatin structure.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Russell Durrett
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Amplified and biobricked from E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The coding region of the gene was isolated via PCR. Biobrick prefix and suffix were added during amplification, and ligated into Ampicillin resistant plasmids.
